  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promotion of Laudato Si&apos; among religious leaders in Asia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CAFOD will support the Federation of Asian Bishop&apos;s Conference to develop a handbook on Laudato Si&apos; for religious leaders in Asia. The handbook will be translated into 10 major Asian languages and aims to raise awareness on climate change and the urgency of the Church&apos;s response to Laudato Si&apos; in the Asian context. The project&apos;s aim is for ordinary Catholics and religious leaders in Asia to have an improved understanding of Laudato Si&apos; and an increased level of engagement with the encyclical. The handbook will be promoted amongst religious and communities leaders across a variety of Asian countries through a series of nationally held TOT workshops and an Asia level workshop, resulting in the development of an Asia climate crisis action plan. This project will build on FABC&apos;s previous project AME002 which aimed at targeting Christian business stakeholders in South and East Asia to increase their commitment to promoting sustainable business practices and tackling climate change.</narrative>
  </description>
